name: Manor Floor Plan
prompt: Authentic 1920s aged yellowed parchment architectural plan of Blackwood Manor. Weathered texture, coffee stains. Top-Down 2D view, North Up. CENTRAL: Long vertical 'Foyer' corridor (North Front Door to South Garden Door). WEST WING (Left): Two rooms, 'Study' (North) and 'Library' (South). Both have doors to Foyer. Door connects Study to Library. EAST WING (Right): Single massive 'Dining Room' running full length of Foyer. Doors connect Dining Room to Foyer. KITCHEN: A geometric 'bump-out' extension attached to the FAR EAST wall of the Dining Room. CRITICAL: Kitchen accessed ONLY via Dining Room. NO Foyer-Kitchen door. SOUTH: Large formal 'Garden'. Vintage ink labels.
